name Lentil Curry with Mango
serves 4
note Serve with rice or naan.
tags main, vegetarian, MENA

# Preparation

- 1 bunch parsley
Wash, shake dry, pick the leaves and chop finely. Set aside.
-> parsley

- 1 clove garlic
@nodep
Peel and chop very finely.
-> garlic

- 30 g ginger
@nodep
Peel and finely grate or chop.
-> ginger

- 4 shallots
@nodep
Peel and finely chop.
-> shallots

- 4 carrots
@nodep
Peel and finely dice.
-> carrots

- 300 g red lentils
- 400 ml vegetable stock
- 200 ml coconut milk
- 2 tbsp butter
- 3 tbsp curry paste
- 2 tsp cumin
- 2 tsp ras el-hanout
- 1 tsp turmeric
- salt
- pepper
= garlic
= ginger
= shallots
= carrots
Heat the butter in a pot and briefly sauté the garlic, ginger, shallots and carrots. Add
the lentils, curry paste, turmeric, cumin and ras el-hanout and sauté briefly. Deglaze
with the stock and bring to a boil. Add the coconut milk, season with salt and pepper and
simmer over low heat for about 10 minutes.
-> curry

- 2 mangoes
@nodep
Peel, remove the flesh from the stone and cut into small cubes.
-> mango

= curry
= mango
= parsley
Reduce the heat to very low, add the mango and parsley and leave to infuse for 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
